      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MIDNIGHT STAR (7) was narrowly beaten when placing two back but missed the frame latest finishing fifth (23.94) in a Mix 2/3 at Richmond. Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide. This looks easier and expected to bounce back. MIGHTY TROJAN (2) filled a minor placing last start at this track behind Woolgoolga Lass (22.62) in a Mix 3/4. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Has performed well from this box with a win and three minor placings to his name from seven starts. Expected to feature. SUTTON BOLT (8) filled a minor placing last start at Goulburn behind Clattered (20.22) in a Mix 1/2/3. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Yet to miss the placings from three starts out of this box. Must be included in calculations. TRIUMPH (1) was in the money last start despite a big quote and is likely to feature again.",
